The paper focuses on natural language understanding (NLU) tasks for the Russian language, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of machine learning models such as ELMo and BERT suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The inclusion of supervised approaches for the tasks suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
